@startuml
title ActiveJob Temporal Cancellation Flow

participant "Developer" as Dev
participant "Rails App" as Rails
participant "Cancel API" as Cancel
participant "Temporal Client" as Client
participant "Temporal Cluster" as Temporal
participant "Worker Process" as Worker
participant "AjRunnerActivity" as Activity

Dev -> Rails: ActiveJob::Temporal.cancel(SendInvoiceJob, "job-uuid-123")
Rails -> Cancel: cancel(SendInvoiceJob, "job-uuid-123")
activate Cancel
Cancel -> Cancel: workflow_id = "ajwf:SendInvoiceJob:job-uuid-123"
note right of Cancel: Deterministic workflow_id = "ajwf:#{job_class}:#{job_id}" ensures handle lookup
Cancel -> Client: client.workflow_handle(workflow_id)
note right of Client: Retrieves workflow handle by workflow_id only
Client -> Temporal: handle.cancel()
note right of Client: Best-effort cancel request sent via Temporal API; no-op if workflow already finished
Cancel --> Rails: request acknowledged
Rails --> Dev: cancellation requested
deactivate Cancel
Temporal -> Worker: deliver cancellation signal to workflow run

alt Activity heartbeating
  Worker -> Activity: cancellation requested (signal)
  Activity -> Temporal: Temporalio::Activity.heartbeat(details)
  Temporal --> Activity: raises CancelledError
  Activity -> Worker: abort job.perform and cleanup
  Worker -> Temporal: report ActivityCancelled
  Temporal --> Client: cancellation acknowledged
else Activity not heartbeating
  note right of Activity: Without heartbeat the activity may finish even after cancel signal
  Activity --> Worker: completes work as normal
  Worker -> Temporal: ActivityCompleted
  Temporal -> Worker: workflow marked Cancelled after completion
end

note over Activity, Temporal: Best-effort cancellation relies on jobs heartbeating periodically for prompt handling
@enduml
